Kim Yong Nam Meets Lao Delegation 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 28 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, met and had a friendly conversation with the delegation of the Laos-Korea Friendship Association led by its Chairman Tong Yeu Tho at the Mansudae Assembly Hall Wednesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  On hand were Mun Jae Chol, acting chairman of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries, officials concerned and Chaleune Warinthrasak, Lao ambassador to the DPRK.

Gift to Kim Jong Il from Lao Delegation  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 28 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il was presented with a gift by the visiting delegation of the Laos-Korea Friendship Association. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was handed today to Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, by Tong Yeu Tho, chairman of the association who is heading the delegation.

Greetings to Chief of Palestinian National Authority 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 28 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, Wednesday sent a message of greetings to Mahmoud Abbas, chairman of the Executive Committee of the Palestine Liberation Organization and chief of the Palestinian National Authority, on the occasion of the "day of world solidarity with the Palestinian people".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Kim Yong Nam in his message noted that the Palestinian people are now waging a vigorous struggle to smash the moves of the hostile forces including Israel to cause internal division and regain the national rights including the right to self-determination and the right to found an independent state. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Reiterating the stand of the government and the people of the DPRK to support the just cause of the Palestinian people, Kim Yong Nam wished the chief success in his work.

Homage Paid to President Kim Il Sung 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 28 (KCNA) -- Participants in the national meeting of intellectuals visited the Kumsusan Memorial Palace on Wednesday to pay homage to President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They went to the sacred temple of Juche with their ardent yearning and boundless reverence for the President, who put forward the intellectuals as a main component of the driving forces of the revolution in his early years, penetrating deep into the position and role to be taken and performed by them in the revolutionary struggle and the building of a new society. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The visitors paid highest tribute to him who advanced the unique policy towards intellectuals and creditably implemented it in the whole historic course of his revolutionary leadership, while taking care of and leading them with warm love and trust.

Vaccination for Children 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 28 (KCNA) -- Vaccination is undertaken under the care of the state in the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@All the therapeutic centers gave various preventive injections to the children of preschool age this year according to their annual inoculation plans. And they took a wide range of health care measures several times to improve the immunity of the children in sight, respiratory system, etc.  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The work for the extermination of intestinal worms was done by the measure of the state. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Work was undertaken for the extermination of intestinal worms among the children under 5 in May and among the school children under 17 in November. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The vaccination for the children was carried out simultaneously at the people's hospitals and clinics, nurseries, kindergartens, primary and middle schools all over the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@In this connection, explanatory materials, materials for propaganda through visual aids, posters and folding propaganda materials on the prevention of various diseases were distributed to the health care centers in the counties, cities and provinces and technical lectures were given to relevant medical workers.

Achievements in Creation of Forests 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 28 (KCNA) -- The DPRK is bending efforts for the creation of forests, registering noticeable results. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The working people serving in afforestation have planted trees in over 66,000 hectares this year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Thus they have made it possible to increase the forest resources of the country under a far-reaching plan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Industrial forest management stations in cities and counties across the country including Kanggye City, Tokchon City and Tongchang County have endeavored to nurse good species of saplings suitable to the local features.  They planted lots of trees in spring and autumn, lifting their rooting rate to more than 80 percent. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Various units including Hoeryong City and Phangyo County industrial forest management stations nursed sturdy saplings by producing large quantities of organic fertilizers in keeping with their specific conditions, while actively introducing a scientific sapling-nursing method. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The Rimyongsu Forestry Station built sapling greenhouses suitable to the local features and produced 400,000 saplings even under the unfavorable climatic condition. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@  In the Tuman River district 700,000-odd fast-growing poplar saplings were grown and sent to industrial forest management stations in North Hamgyong and Ryanggang Provinces.

Heavily Armed (Mail-Clad) Cavalrymen of Koguryo 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 28 (KCNA) -- The Korean nation made distinguished development in armament in the Middle Ages. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Koguryo (277 B.C.- 668 A.D.), a powerful state which existed for a thousand years, always inflicted wholesale deaths on the enemies in battles against foreign invaders by forming units of heavily armed cavalrymen in which not only the soldiers but also the horses were clad in armor. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Koguryo inherited the developed iron processing art of Ancient Korea, which it widely introduced into arms. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is well illustrated by the models of horses in armor found in the historical remain in Chol Pass, Kangwon Province, tomb mural paintings of the Koguryo period such as the tomb murals of the Yaksu-ri, King Kogukwon's Mausoleum, the twin-pillared tomb, etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The models of horses and tomb murals vividly depict the then soldiers wearing helmets, coats of mail with sleeves reaching the tips of the hands and trousers long enough to reach the tiptoes. They also show horses wearing helmets and armors with the hems reaching their carpi. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was in 246 that the first armored unit was hurled into a battle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Very strong in attack and defense capacity, the armored unit in the middle ages could strike a smashing blow to the invaders. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The world's first heavily armed (mail-clad) unit was organized and effectively used in battles against invaders in the period of Koguryo. This was one of the important factors of Koguryo becoming the great power in the East.

U.S. Ambition for Military Supremacy under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 28 (KCNA) -- It is the invariable design of the U.S. bellicose forces to dominate the world by force, Rodong Sinmun today says in a signed commentary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It has been proven more evidently by their recent evermore frenzied and reckless moves, the signed commentary notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 According to news report, the recent conference of the U.S. Senate approved the military budget for the fiscal 2008 amounting to 459 billion U.S. dollars. Big portion of this fund will be diverted to the production of a space bomber called "Falcon." The U.S. warlike forces are scheming to deploy this new type of space bomber for attack in their mainland and promptly strike and destroy any targets on the globe. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What should not be overlooked is the fact that the U.S. war hawks are busying themselves developing HCV (hypersonic cruise vehicle) allegedly to mount preemptive attack on what they call nuclear-launching pads in some countries, including the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The fact goes to prove that they zealously seek to contain those countries refusing to fawn upon the U.S. and gratify their ambition for world supremacy by accelerating the development and production of new space arms to secure the military edge. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 To attain the above-said aims, they have also been hell-bent on increasing modern nuclear arms such as development of smaller nukes, with continued investment of colossal amount of money, disregarding the just demand of the international community for nuclear disarmament. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Some time ago, a spokesman for the Missile Defense Agency of the U.S. Department of Defense announced that the U.S. deployed tens of interceptor missiles aiming at north Korea in Alaska and California. This is an undisguised military provocation and threat and blackmail to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is busy with the arms buildup and the moves to provoke a war while reinforcing armaments on a large scale to realize its wild ambition for military supremacy and domination over the world. As a result, the situation is getting strained and the danger of war is increasing in different areas of the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. warlike forces should discard their anachronistic design to grab military supremacy and hold sway over the world.

Intellectuals Called for Performing Great Feats in Building Great Prosperous Powerful Nation
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 28 (KCNA) -- The intellectuals in the DPRK are the ardent revolutionaries who have made a long journey of the Songun revolution under the leadership of the great Workers' Party of Korea and patriotic fighters who have gone through thick and thin in hearty response to the call of the Party and the country. Rodong Sinmun Wednesday says this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the intellectuals grown up under the care of the great Party have become a mighty force for the building of a great prosperous powerful nation, the signed article goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The history in which the DPRK has grown strong and prosperous despite all sorts of ordeals is the one in which the DPRK has achieved great victories and brought about epoch-making changes thanks to the might of the writing brush as well as powerful arms. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The revolutionary intellectuals in the DPRK have performed uninterrupted heroic feats in every period of the revolution and construction and at every stage of them under the guidance of the great leader and the great Party since the outset of the Korean revolution. The path covered by the Korean intellectuals since their meeting held 15 years ago occupies a particularly important place in this proud history. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The past 15 years are a shining one during which all the intellectuals have been trained as revolutionary fighters of Kim Jong Il, keenly realizing the validity of the Songun line and Songun politics of the Party, and a proud one during which they together with all the servicepersons of the People's Army and people have brought the dawn of a great prosperous powerful nation to this land, turning adversity into favorable conditions and misfortune into blessings in the revolutionary soldier spirit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Our intellectuals are strong in faith and will as they firmly believe in their leader only and follow him in whatever storm and stress. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their revolutionary faith in the present era precisely means their faith in their leader. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Our intellectuals are soldiers and disciples of Kim Jong Il who are entirely entrusting their destinies to him. Korean-style socialism is sure to triumph and they can work any epoch-making miracles as long as they are led by him. This is the unshakable faith they enshrined while following him. Having this faith, they made it possible for the country to become a proud possessor of a satellite and built lots of modern production bases and monumental edifices in different parts of the country by devoting their all wisdom and enthusiasm in the worst adversity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Our intellectuals are the genuine Songun revolutionary comrades of Kim Jong Il who are sharing the same destiny with him despite rain or snow. It is the biggest privilege for our intellectuals transparent in faith in the leader to be an eternal companion, loyal helper and best adviser of the Party. Herein lie the great honor and pride of our intellectuals who have formed an unbreakable harmonious whole with Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Intellectuals are advocates of justice and pioneers of society. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Our intellectuals are vanguard fighters in the Songun era who have firmly equipped themselves with the Songun idea and dedicated their all to the victory of the Songun revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Invulnerable are the politico-ideological position and military position of Korean-style socialism. This would be unthinkable without the devoted struggle of our intellectuals. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Our intellectuals have performed proud feats in glorifying the country as an invincible one with strong military power. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They are standard-bearers in the struggle to make the shortcut to the building of a great prosperous powerful nation with their ardent patriotic enthusiasm and rich technological and cultural knowledge. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There may be something difficult to be done by our intellectuals but there is nothing impossible for them as they have been tempered and nurtured ardent patriotism on the road of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people are making a dynamic advance to greet the morning of a great prosperous powerful nation, full of conviction and optimism, having a huge unit of able intellectuals. This is entirely possible because they have Kim Jong Il at the head of the Party and the revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Now the vast ranks of the Korean intellectuals are displaying their tremendous might in the building of a great prosperous powerful nation. This would be unthinkable without Kim Jong Il's great politics of attaching importance to writing brush and intellectuals. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He has successfully inherited the noble intention of the President who unrolled the political history of attaching importance to writing brush, making sure that the flag of the WPK was emblazoned with a hammer and a sickle along with a writing brush before its founding, thus building the ranks of intellectuals and steering the Songun revolution in reliance upon their might. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The WPK's policy for intellectuals is the most revolutionary one as it calls for settling all issues arising in the revolution and construction by deeply trusting the ranks of intellectuals as a driving force of the revolution and relying on them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il's trust in our intellectuals is undisputed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Our intellectuals will remain in sky-high spirit and our country surely reach the high eminence of a great prosperous powerful nation in the near future as long as he leads the powerful ranks of intellectuals and instills immense confidence and courage into them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the most important task facing the intellectuals of Songun Korea at present to give fullest play to their stamina in the building of an economic power as they have performed great feats in the struggle to build an ideological and military power. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The article calls on them to live up to the WPK's political trust with great technological achievements.

S. Korean Military Authorities' Submission to U.S. Assailed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 28 (KCNA) -- The South Headquarters of the National Alliance for the Country's Reunification and the People for Achieving Peace and Reunification in south Korea reportedly called a joint press conference in front of the Defence Ministry building in Seoul on Nov. 22 to denounce the pro-American submissive behavior of the military authorities seeking to purchase the scrap ammunitions of the U.S. forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the military authorities conducted a "performance test" of the ammunitions scrapped by the U.S. forces present in south Korea and opened its results to the press, speakers said at the conference: The "test" was made when the authorities were rushing the work to take over the war supplies from the U.S. forces in south Korea. It is nothing but a perfunctory play to justify the purchase of the war supplies which are little different from rubbish. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The authorities are planning to spend trillions of won for the purchase of the above-said war supplies, asserting that they can be used for good as they have been treasured, the speakers pointed out, declaring that they would not pardon the U.S., who usurps the tremendous tax collected from the south Korean people in return for its waste ammunitions, and the Defence Ministry kowtowing to the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After the conference the members of the organizations staged a protest, throwing eggs at the signboard of the ministry. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, fishermen residing around the combined firing-range in Thaean County, South Chungchong Province, where the "test" was conducted, strongly urged the military authorities to make compensation for the damage.

Joint Seminar on Songun Policy Held in Nigeria 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 28 (KCNA) -- A joint seminar on the Songun policy took place in Abuja of Nigeria on Nov. 15. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 M. M. Alhassan, chairman of the Nigerian National Committee for the Study of the Juche Idea, at the seminar made a report titled "The great Songun policy is an ever-victorious banner" and several other figures spoke on the subjects of "The historical background against which the Songun policy was set forth", "The reality of Korea where the Songun policy is in force ", etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter and speakers referred to the fact that upon embarking on the road of revolution in his early years President Kim Il Sung fathered the Juche idea and the Songun idea through a practical struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They noted that Kim Jong Il has further developed in depth the Songun idea in the course of leading the revolution and construction and enforced the original Songun policy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Songun policy calls for putting forward the army as the main force of the revolution and carrying out the revolution and construction in reliance upon it, they said, noting: By thoroughly implementing this policy the DPRK could firmly protect the sovereignty of the country and the dignity of the people and bring about the dawn of a great prosperous powerful nation in the most difficult period. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They stressed that today the Songun idea and policy serve as the guidelines to be consistently held fast to by the world progressives desirous of independence and as an ever-lasting banner of victory.

Ri Hoe Chang's Ambition to Grab Power Assailed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 28 (KCNA) -- Kwon Chon Sik, chairman of the United Confederation of Koreans in the Far Eastern Region of Russia, released a statement on Nov. 21 assailing political imposter Ri Hoe Chang's ambition to wrest power. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Accusing Ri, human scum, of running amuck to come to power in south Korea, making a mockery of the justice and conscience oblivious of his crime-woven past, the statement branded Ri as a die-hard anti-reunification element, a political charlatan and a kingpin of irregularities and corruption. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is nothing but a daydream for this despicable guy to try hard to take the "presidential office" in a bid to gratify his greed for power, the statement noted, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ri is a pro-U.S. sycophantic traitor who kowtows towards the U.S. and human scum as he embezzled truck loads of money amounting to astronomical figures and accumulated wealth through all sorts of irregularities and swindles. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We Koreans overseas bitterly denounce Ri for recklessly perpetrating acts of treachery quite contrary to the trend of the June 15 era and will actively turn out in the struggle to throw overboard dregs of history.

Se inicia II ronda de conversaciones entre titulares militares Norte-Sur
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 28 de noviembre (ATCC) -- Comenzo el dia 27 en esta capital la segunda ronda de conversaciones entre los ministros de Fuerzas Armadas del Norte y el Sur de Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En esta ocasion participaron la delegacion de la parte Norte encabezada por el ministro de las Fuerzas Armadas Populares, Kim Il Chol, y la delegacion de la parte Sur presidida por el ministro de Defensa y delegado-jefe Kim Jang Su. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Ambas partes discutieron las medidas militares para la ejecucion de la "Declaracion para el Desarrollo de las Relaciones Norte-Sur, la Paz y la Prosperidad".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El jefe de la delegacion nortena dijo que para ejecutar consecuentemente la historica Declaracion del 4 de Octubre es importante sobre todo tener correcta concepcion del problema de la paz del pais y continuo: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Ante todo, es preciso comprender que el problema de la paz de Corea es un asunto para eliminar la tension y confrontacion militares y prevenir el peligro de la guerra. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En segundo lugar, debemos entender que el problema mencionado es el mas apremiante que debe ser solucionado con mayor prioridad entre todos los problemas que surgen entre el Norte y el Sur. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Ademas, hay que tener una nueva concepcion de que el problema de la paz de Corea debe ser solucionado conforme a la exigencia de la epoca de reunificacion iniciada el 15 de junio. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  A continuacion, aclaro la posicion de principios del Ejercito Popular de Corea sobre las medidas militares que se presentan en la ejecucion de la historica Declaracion del 4 de Octubre y presento los remedios para materializarlas: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Primero, las autoridades militares de ambas partes deben tomar medidas sustanciales para poner fin a las relaciones militares hostiles y asegurar el aflojamiento de la tension y la paz. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Segundo, las autoridades militares de ambas partes deben tomar medidas practicas para rechazar la guerra y observar consecuentemente las obligaciones de no-agresion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Tercero, las autoridades militares de ambas partes deben cooperarse en el campo militar para que los jefes de Estado, vinculados a la eliminacion del sistema de armisticio y a la implantacion del sistema de paz, puedan declarar cuanto antes el fin de la guerra. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Cuarto, las autoridades militares de ambas partes deben tomar las medidas para asegurar en lo militar las labores de cooperacion e intercambio Norte-Sur. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Por ultimo, Kim Il Chol exhorto a las autoridades militares de ambas partes a unir las fuerzas con el espiritu de "entre nosotros, los connacionales" previendo no solo el presente sino tambien el futuro de la nacion coreana para hacer gran aporte a la paz del pais, al relajamiento de la tension militar y al desarrollo de las relaciones Norte-Sur en su conjunto. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Le siguio en usar la palabra el delegado-jefe de la parte Sur. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Las conversaciones continuan.

Kim Jong Il recibe presente de delegacion lao
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 28 de noviembre (ATCC) -- El Dirigente Kim Jong Il recibio presente que le dirigiera la delegacion de la Asociacion de Amistad Laos-Corea presidida por su presidente Tong Yeu Tho, de visita en Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@El jefe de la delegacion lo traslado este miercoles a Kim Yong Nam, presidente del Presidium de la Asamblea Popular Suprema de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea.

Intelectuales rinden tributo a Kim Il Sung
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 28 de noviembre (ATCC) -- Los participantes en la Conferencia Nacional de Intelectuales rindieron este miercoles el mas sublime homenaje al Presidente Kim Il Sung en el Palacio Memorial Kumsusan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Ellos acudieron a ese supremo lugar del Juche con gran anoranza e infinita veneracion hacia el Presidente quien al percatarse de la posicion y papel que juegan los intelectuales en la lucha revolucionaria y la construccion de una nueva sociedad, los presento como uno de los principales integrantes del sujeto de la revolucion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Ademas, el Presidente presento y ejecuto una original politica de intelectuales en todo el curso historico de su direccion sobre la revolucion, atendio y condujo a estos con calido amor y gran confianza.
